## 🎯 USAGE INSTRUCTIONS

### **Before Workshop:**
1. **Set up workshop details** in Sheet 1
2. **Import participant data** or add manually
3. **Baseline assessment** - Record starting skill levels
4. **Environmental baseline** - Record current cooking methods

### **During Workshop:**
1. **Real-time data entry** - Track participation and engagement
2. **Carbon tracking** - Monitor energy and waste reduction
3. **Skill observation** - Note improvements and challenges
4. **Cultural documentation** - Record heritage elements taught

### **After Workshop:**
1. **Post-workshop assessment** - Measure skill improvements
2. **Final carbon calculation** - Total environmental impact
3. **AI analysis** - Review automated insights and recommendations
4. **Report generation** - Create participant and executive reports

---

## 🌟 AI INSIGHTS EXAMPLES

### **Environmental Impact:**
> "This workshop reduced carbon footprint by 47% compared to traditional cooking methods. The biggest impact came from energy-efficient cooking techniques which saved 2.3 kWh per participant."

### **Cultural Preservation:**
> "Traditional Jollof Rice techniques were preserved at 92% authenticity while introducing sustainable adaptations. Participants showed 85% improvement in cultural knowledge retention."

### **Skill Development:**
> "Participants improved cooking efficiency by 63% on average. The most significant gains were in knife skills (78% improvement) and energy awareness (71% improvement)."

### **Financial Impact:**
> "Smart-Prep methods resulted in 34% cost savings per participant. Long-term ROI projection shows 285% return over 12 months through continued sustainable practices."

